{
  "id": 30040,
  "kuerzel": "M_SE1",
  "bezeichnung": "Software-Engineering 1",
  "kreditpunkte": 4,
  "lernziele": "<p>All participants are able to explain and apply the selected software engineering practices within a software development project effectively, using modern state-of-the-art methods and tools.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Selected practices from the following disciplines will be covered:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Business modelling</li>\n<li>Requirements</li>\n<li>Analysis and design</li>\n<li>Verification</li>\n<li>Deployment</li>\n<li>Configuration and change management</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The taxonomy and format of the Rational Unified Process (RUP) and the Unified Modelling Language (UML) will be used as a basis whenever appropriate.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
  "vorausgKenntnisse": "<p>Englische Sprachkenntnisse</p>\n<p>(Dieses Modul wird auf Englisch durchgef&uuml;hrt.)</p>",
  "semesterBewertung": "keine Note oder Wertung",
  "sprache": "de-CH",
  "zustand": "deaktiviert",
  "kurse": [
    {
      "id": 30041,
      "kuerzel": "SE1",
      "bezeichnung": "Software-Engineering 1",
      "lernziele": "<p>Refer to the learning goals for the module.</p>",
      "planinhalt": "<p>The following software engineering practices will be covered:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Version control (git)</li>\n<li>Continuous integration</li>\n<li>Domain Analysis and Modelling</li>\n<li>Requirements Elicitation and Specification (Functional (Use Cases) &amp; Non-Functional)</li>\n<li>Modelling System Behaviour (UML State Machine Diagrams and Activity Diagrams)</li>\n<li>Error Handling Design</li>\n<li>Design by Contract</li>\n<li>Code Metrics</li>\n<li>Software Testing (Unit, Integration &amp; System Tests; Test Design)</li>\n<li>Static Software Analysis and Verification</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This course will be taught in English.</p>",
